" <div class=\"graphic\">",
"  <div class=\"figure\" style=\"width: 561px\">",
"   <div class=\"ttl\">",
"    Pheochromocytoma in the adrenal gland",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 541px; height: 288px; background-image: url(data:image/jpeg;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    Magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) findings in adrenal pheochromocytomas. Left panel: Sagittal MRI demonstrates a mass (white arrow) displacing the inferior vena cava anteriorly (black arrow). This caval displacement is typically seen with tumors arising in the adrenal gland. Right panel: Coronal MRI of the abdomen demonstrates a large mass in the right adrenal bed (arrow), lying immediately superior to the kidney. The low signal intensity in the center is caused by hemorrhage into the tumor.",
